task.summary: Default task

Created sample_data.py, which downloads a variety of data, maps them all to the same 5 minute intervals, and exports that data to a .nc file
Added an extra optional argument to get_xxx_data, which allows them to be binned into 5 minute intervals
Added expand_5min, which creates extra data points every 5 minutes for Kp data, which has 1 data point per 3 hours base
Added comments to expand_5min
Fixed variable names
Fixed a bug where get_omni_data was creating duplicate values at the beginning of each month, crashing sample_data.py
Updated comments
Fixed comments

Added standard deviation values to the bin_5min function, so that anything that gets binned creates both a mean and a standard deviation dataArray to be stored in the complete data
Added comments saying that omni cannot get standard deviation values (at least easily), as it is binned in the omni package, and not through my own function
Removed print statement

Added shift argument in cart2polar, which allows the user to shift the angle by any amount (in radians)
Added flag for whether the file that data should be binned at exists or not, allowing the user to mix the new data with existing data of a file with the same name
Updated comments

Added shift argument in cart2polar, which allows the user to shift the angle by any amount (in radians)
Added flag for whether the file that data should be binned at exists or not, allowing the user to mix the new data with existing data of a file with the same name
Updated comments
Removed accidental print statement
Fixed Standard Deviation values by adding a square root

Created the file creating_edi_maps, which uses the functions from plot_nc_data to plot the electric field, count, and potential of a file containing an xarray
Created the plot_potential function
Renamed some functions in plot_nc_data to avoid confusion
Moved the calculate potential functions to data_manipulation, so they can be used easier

Created function expand_kp, which is a significantly more versatile version of the function expand_5min.
Changed get_kp_data to use expand_kp, and the expand argument now takes the time that the user wants the kp data to be formatted to
Changed sample_data.py to work correctly with the updated get_kp_data
Casted some variables to float64 from float32 in various get_xxx_data functions to prevent memory overflow errors
Added/reworded comments

Created function expand_kp, which is a significantly more versatile version of the function expand_5min.
Changed get_kp_data to use expand_kp, and the expand argument now takes the time that the user wants the kp data to be formatted to
Changed sample_data.py to work correctly with the updated get_kp_data
Casted some variables to float64 from float32 in various get_xxx_data functions to prevent memory overflow errors
Added/reworded comments

Created storage_objects.py, which holds container classes for different variables, which helps cut down on number of arguments.
Added/corrected comments

Refactored store_efield_data to take an extra argument that allows the user to bin other values along with the electric field. Currently only supports Kp, but was redone to easily support other options
Edited a couple names of variables in store_efield_data result, and changed plot_nc_data to accomodate this
Edited comments
Fixed get_edp_data in download_data so that it no longer breaks with the newest version of pymms
Re-uploaded creating_edi_maps.py and storage_objects.py in git

Updated Comments
Made plot_potential more reliable
Updated Comments

Implemented the driving parameter argument, which will take the data points that want to be binned and separate them by a desired parameter. Note that this is not entirely implemented, as it will not separate the extra data, only the electric field data.
Updated comments

Updated store_efield_data to utilize the driving_parameter argument correctly with different parameters, and (hopefully) have it separate the extra data when that argument is not empty.
Updated comments

Corrected the driving parameter binning, as the values were getting exponentially smaller the longer the program was run. The output also includes a count value for each separated variable when using a driving parameter
Updated Comments
Fixed the driving parameter count for real this time

Implemented some of the IEF storing stuff.
Created creating_Kp_plots, which creates a couple different plots corresponding to plots from Rowland 1998 using given data collected from store_efield_data
Updated comments

Implemented Counts in each L range at each Kp bin in creating_Kp_plots.py
Minor tweaks elsewhere

Allowed for expand_kp to take either datetime or datetime64 objects
Updated Kp_plots to have axes and such
Fixed get_IEF to work correctly
Updated comments

Added calculate_potential_2 to data_manipulation.py, which finds the potential using scipy.optimize.minimize instead of using the solved for equation. Should be the same answer as calculate_potential, but is slightly different.
Updated comments
Fixed a bug that caused store_efield_data.py to sometimes crash when using a driving parameter.
No longer requires the user to include the file extension when giving a name for the output file

Added a file called requirements.txt, which contains all the required packages for all the files in the graphs folder.
Remodeled creating_edi_maps.py to use arguments. Also improved functionality to include polar vs cartesian differences and outputting the potential data to a csv file.
Added another argument to plot_efield_cartesian and plot_efield_polar in plot_nc_data.py to include a choice of variable that is being plotted.
Updated comments

Separated create_timestamps into two functions, one for creating the timestamps (still named create_timestamps), and one for acquiring 5-minute bin times in a given range, named get_5min_times.
Updated comments

Created a new file called unified_efield.py, which is going to be where I create the electric field approximation using the method of Bortnik:2016. Right now it has the framework for organizing the required data into a pytorch tensor object.
Created a new reference file: TorchDataset. It contains an example of a user-made dataset used for creating neural networks in PyTorch

Updated unified_efield.py such that the neural network runs, but does not create a good model.
Updated Comments

Added a log argument to create_cartesian_plot and create_polar_plot so that the output will be logarithmic instead of linear.
Kp plots is still a disaster. It exists.
Updated Comments

Took all plots from creating_Kp_plots.py, enhanced their functionality, removed unneeded arguments, and moved them to plot_nc_data.py.
creating_Kp_plots.py is now like creating_edi_maps.py, which uses the functions that are now located in plot_nc_data.py and uses them with inputted data to create plots.
Updated comments

Fixed sample_data.py such that all the data is outputted to the same file, instead of 1 .nc and one undefined file.
Fixed plot_nc_data.py so that the values are plotted the correct direction.
Updated comments

Combined plot_efield_cartesian and plot_efield_polar in plot_nc_data.py into one function, plot_efield, with less arguments, and an additional optional mode argument (which is cartesian or polar). Wherever either of these functions were used have been replaced with the new plot_efield function
Added an extra line in remove_spacecraft_efield and remove_corot_efield so that they both take out the respective efield from the E_GSE variable, but also creates a new variable in the xarray object, called E_sc and E_corot respectively
Updated Comments

Changed remove_corot_efield to use an updated value, using the same method from the jupyter notebook.
Updated Comments

remove_corot_efield and remove_spacecraft_efield now assume that remove_spacecraft_efield is run first, and these functions now save the electric field that they modify as an additional variable in the dataset. (original_E_GSE and no_spacecraft_E_GSE)
fixed a bug in create_timestamps that caused incorrect binning on daylight savings days
Updated Comments

removed the ability to input hours/minutes/seconds in sample_data and store_efield_data, since putting anything other than 00:00:00 can potentially cause problems. New format is YYYY-MM-DD (e.g. 2015-09-10)
Created get_dst_data, which gets all the dst data over a desired time range, and bins the data into 5 minute intervals if the user wants. Known issue: if the directory data/dst/ does not already exist, it will break. simply make the folder to fix this
Increased functionality of read_txt_files to be used with dst as well as kp
added get_dst_data to sample_data.py
Updated Comments

Created predict_unified_efield, which takes a given time and a trained pytorch NN and predicts the electric field and the electric potential, and creates some plots of the resulting values.
Uploading test_model_to_beat.pth, which is a NN created by unified_efield. As more data points are gathered and the NN is improved, this file will be updated to reflect that.
Uploading 090115_033022_mm1_sample_data.nc, which is a file created by sample data, run from September 1st, 2015 to March 30, 2022, which contains electric field data from the mms1 probe.
Updated unified_efield, such that it actually works. It now requires a file from sample_data that has downloaded the electric field, Kp, and Dst
Enhanced bin_5min such that it now takes any amount of time and creates 5 minute bins as long as the inputted time range is a multiple of 5 minutes. This is not a problem if any of the get_xxx_functions is used, as they automatically add whatever time is needed onto the end of the time range such that the time range is a multiple of 5 minutes
Fixed read_txt_files so that it works for all ranges of Dst time ranges
Updated Comments

Created predict_unified_efield, which takes a given time and a trained pytorch NN and predicts the electric field and the electric potential, and creates some plots of the resulting values.
Updated unified_efield, such that it actually works. It now requires a file from sample_data that has downloaded the electric field, Kp, and Dst
Enhanced bin_5min such that it now takes any amount of time and creates 5 minute bins as long as the inputted time range is a multiple of 5 minutes. This is not a problem if any of the get_xxx_functions is used, as they automatically add whatever time is needed onto the end of the time range such that the time range is a multiple of 5 minutes
Fixed read_txt_files so that it works for all ranges of Dst time ranges
Updated Comments

Created the IMEF_main branch, which will hold both the electric field and electric potential work, along with the magnetic field models and particle tracing work. This push gives the electric field and electric potential code.
Added placeholder files so that the bfield and particle tracing directories are on git
Added placeholder files so that the bfield and particle tracing directories are on git
Fixed get_aspoc_data
